![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/df3e492b-4b3a-4a72-81bf-17d778d620a4/20250227_113634.jpg)

According to sources within WWE's creative team, Randy Orton is expected to make his return to the ring by next month. This news comes via PWInsider, who spoke with multiple sources within the WWE.

The current plan is for Orton to be back in action in time for WWE's European tour, which will take place prior to WrestleMania 41. This tour will likely see Orton reinserted into the WWE storyline, potentially setting up a major feud or match for the upcoming WrestleMania event.

Fans of the Viper will be eagerly awaiting his return, and it will be interesting to see how WWE chooses to reintegration him into the fold.